Disciplinary Officials Meet to Mark CPC's Birthday 
The Central Commission for Discipline Inspection of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) and the Ministry of Supervision jointly held a gathering
Friday, to mark the 80th anniversary of the founding of the CPC.
Present at the meeting was Wei Jianxing, a member of the Standing
Committee of the CPC Central Committee Political Bureau, who is also
secretary of the CPC Central Committee Secretariat, and secretary of
the CPC Central Commission for Discipline Inspection.
A number of the units and individuals from the departments were
rewarded for their meritorious conduct.
Cao Qingze, an executive deputy secretary of the CPC Central Commission
for Discipline Inspection, presided over and addressed the gathering.
The Party's 80 year history proves that strict and impartial discipline
and good style are the keys for ensuring the success of the Party's
cause, the official said.
